==Calculators==
===Open Social Security=== * [https://opensocialsecurity.com/ Open Social Security] is a free, open-source Social Security strategy calculator that helps you decide which Social Security claiming strategy will get you the most dollars over your lifetime. Created by [[Mike Piper]]. Support is provided in {{Forum post|t=251065|title="Open Social Security" calculator: feature requests, bug reports, etc.}}
==Wiki articles== * [[Retiree Portfolio Model]], by forum member BigFoot48. A spreadsheet that includes a feature that compares two alternative SS benefit amounts and starting ages, including the ability to include the File and Suspend option for those still eligible, and determines the impact of the alternatives upon income, taxes and portfolio balances. *[[Social Security payment deductions]], sscritic via ObliviousInvestor ([[Mike Piper]]). Provides the legal basis for Medicare premium deductions and federal taxes withheld from your Social Security monthly payment. The legal basis for rounding the payment amount is also described. Examples are provided. *[[Social Security tax impact calculator]], by forum member PapaGeek, graphically shows how the taxation of your Social Security (SS) benefits will affect your retirement tax rates.
==Forum discussions== *{{Forum post|t=262772 | title = Downloadable Social Security Benefit Estimator| author=neurosphere| date = Oct 31, 2018}}. (Regularly updated with up-to-date versions). Provides ballpark estimates of social security benefits, as well as allow you to simulate the effects of future price and wage inflation in order to convert benefits more "accurately" into "today's dollars". * {{Forum post|t=253720|title=Effect of Social Security when Retiring before Benefits Begin|author=#Cruncher|date=Jul 11, 2018}}. When retiring ''before'' starting Social Security, determine how much savings are needed to fund a desired level of spending. Instructions and examples are provided to create your own spreadsheet. * {{Forum post|p=4587454|title=Re: <nowiki>[Calculating future Social Security benefits: How do I adjust the discount rate?]</nowiki>| author=#Cruncher |date=Jun 10, 2019 }}. Calculates the present value (PV) of expected Social Security benefits. The created table approximates the results from the [https://opensocialsecurity.com/ Open Social Security] calculator (see the above forum discussion). *{{Forum post|t=255206|title=SocialSecurity.tools updated to include spousal benefits |author =gregable |date=Jul 30, 2018}}. A free and open-source calculator which estimates your future benefits from your [https://blog.ssa.gov/why-it-pays-to-keep-a-careful-eye-on-your-earnings-record/ earnings record]. ===Lieutenant.Columbo=== *{{Forum post|t=199103|title=Social Security <nowiki>[i]</nowiki>: Max SS Earnings, Bend Points, How Many More Years? <nowiki>[USA]</nowiki>|date=Sep 08, 2016}} *{{Forum post|t=199254|title=Social Security <nowiki>[ii]</nowiki>: 2nd Bend And Retirement At Age 56, What PIA Claiming At Age 70? <nowiki>[USA]</nowiki>|date=Sep 10, 2016}} *{{Forum post|t=199278|title=Social Security <nowiki>[iii]</nowiki>: Spouses <nowiki>[USA]</nowiki>|date=Sep 10, 2016}}
